Henry Varian Daly (20 July 1838 – 3 June 1925) was an Anglican archdeacon in Ireland in the late nineteenth and early twentieth centuries.
Daly was educated at Trinity College, Dublin. He was ordained in  1861; and served curacies in Waterford, Ballinasloe and Killinane. He was Rector of Gort from 1874; the last discrete Archdeacon of Clonfert from 1881,  and  Archdeacon of Kilmacduagh from 1891, holding all three positions until his death.

response: The Archdeacon of Clonfert was a senior ecclesiastical officer within the Diocese of Clonfert until 1625;  the Diocese of Clonfert and Kilmacduagh until 1834"Fasti Ecclesiae Hibernicae: The succession of the prelates Volume 4" Cotton,H. pp180-182 Dublin, Hodges & Smith, 1848-1878 when it became an office within the Diocese of Killaloe and Clonfert. The Archdeaconry can trace its history from Meiler De Burgo who held office from 1550 to 1587 through to the last discrete incumbent Henry Varian Daly who died in 1925.
